{
  "text": "The Adinkra for this is an N -dimensional cube. To see this, we note that the basis elements are labeled by x ∈ {0, 1} N , the vertices of the N -dimensional cube. The edges colored I connect x to x I, which changes the I th coordinate. The supermultiplet specified by Eqs. (7.5) was called the \"base bosonic Clifford Algebra superfield\" in Ref. [CITATION_1] . To emphasize its chromotopology, we will refer to this as the \"Colored N -cube Clifford supermultiplet\".",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "18179363"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "18179363": {
      "title": "Adinkras: A graphical technology for supersymmetric representation theory",
      "abstract": "We present a symbolic method for organizing the representation theory of one-dimensional superalgebras. This relies on special objects, which we have called adinkra symbols, which supply tangible geometric forms to the still-emerging mathematical basis underlying supersymmetry."
    }
  }
}